Further information concerning the Scottish Church missions in British Central Africa may be found in South Africa: The English People Overseas, Volume VI, by A. Wyatt Tilby;
The Story of the Rhodesias and Nyasaland and The Beginnings of Nyasaland and North-Eastern Rhodesia, 1859-95, by A. J. Hanna; Nyasaland and Northern Rhodesia: Corridor to the North by Norman H. Pollock, Jr.; and, The Shire Highlands (East Central Africa) As Colony and Mission, by
John Buchanan (with preface by James Rankin). These books, as well as others about Nyasaland, can be found in the Library.
